# Virtual Coupon Usage Tracker Plugin - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a WordPress plugin that tracks virtual coupon usage with order IDs, shows reasons for missing order IDs, and provides AJAX pagination. It's designed to be compatible with WooCommerce HPOS (High-Performance Order Storage).

## Code Standards & Conventions

### PHP Standards
- Follow WordPress Coding Standards
- Use proper WordPress hooks and filters
- Always sanitize and validate input data
- Use prepared statements for database queries
- Implement proper error handling with try-catch blocks
- Use WordPress nonce verification for AJAX requests
- Check user capabilities before allowing actions

### File Structure
```
virtual-coupon-usage-tracker/
├── virtual-coupon-usage-tracker.php (main plugin file)
├── includes/
│   ├── class-vcut-database.php (database operations)
│   ├── class-vcut-admin.php (admin interface)
│   └── class-vcut-ajax.php (AJAX handlers)
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── admin.css (admin styles)
│   └── js/
│       └── admin.js (admin JavaScript)
└── .cursorrules (this file)
```

### Naming Conventions
- Plugin prefix: `VCUT_` for classes, `vcut_` for functions
- CSS classes: `vcut-` prefix (kebab-case)
- JavaScript: camelCase for variables and functions
- Database tables: Use WordPress prefix + `acfw_virtual_coupons`
- AJAX actions: `vcut_` prefix

### Security Best Practices
- Always verify nonces in AJAX requests
- Check user capabilities (`manage_woocommerce`)
- Sanitize all input data using WordPress functions
- Escape output data when displaying
- Use prepared statements for database queries
- Validate date formats and other input types

### HPOS Compatibility
- Always check if HPOS is enabled before using order tables
- Use `\Automattic\WooCommerce\Utilities\OrderUtil::custom_orders_table_usage_is_enabled()`
- Provide fallback queries for legacy post-based orders
- Use appropriate order edit links based on HPOS status

### Database Operations
- Use WordPress `$wpdb` global for database operations
- Always use prepared statements with `$wpdb->prepare()`
- Handle both HPOS and legacy order storage
- Implement proper error handling for database queries
- Use transactions for bulk operations when needed

### AJAX Implementation
- Use WordPress AJAX hooks (`wp_ajax_` and `wp_ajax_nopriv_`)
- Always verify nonces and check user permissions
- Return proper JSON responses using `wp_send_json_success()` and `wp_send_json_error()`
- Handle both success and error cases in JavaScript
- Implement loading states and error messages

### Frontend Assets
- Enqueue scripts and styles properly using WordPress hooks
- Use versioning for cache busting
- Localize JavaScript with translation strings and AJAX URLs
- Only load assets on relevant admin pages
- Use WordPress admin styles for consistency

### Responsive Design
- Use flexbox for layout components
- Implement mobile-first responsive design
- Make tables scrollable on mobile devices
- Use appropriate breakpoints for different screen sizes
- Test on various devices and screen sizes

### Error Handling
- Implement proper error handling in all functions
- Use WordPress error handling patterns
- Provide meaningful error messages to users
- Log errors for debugging when appropriate
- Handle edge cases gracefully

### Performance Considerations
- Use pagination for large datasets (20 items per page)
- Implement efficient database queries with proper indexing
- Use AJAX for dynamic content loading
- Minimize database queries where possible
- Cache results when appropriate

### Accessibility
- Use proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure keyboard navigation works properly
- Provide alternative text for icons
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Test with screen readers

### Testing Guidelines
- Test with both HPOS enabled and disabled
- Test with different user roles and capabilities
- Test AJAX functionality thoroughly
- Test responsive design on various devices
- Test with large datasets for performance
- Test error scenarios and edge cases

### Documentation
- Document all functions and classes with proper PHPDoc
- Include parameter types and return values
- Document complex logic and algorithms
- Keep README up to date with installation and usage instructions
- Document any dependencies or requirements

### WordPress Integration
- Use WordPress admin menu system
- Follow WordPress admin UI patterns
- Use WordPress color schemes and styling
- Implement proper plugin activation/deactivation hooks
- Use WordPress translation functions for internationalization

### Version Control
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Tag releases appropriately
- Maintain a changelog
- Use branching strategy for features and fixes

## Development Workflow
1. Always test locally before committing
2. Check for PHP errors and warnings
3. Validate HTML and CSS
4. Test JavaScript functionality
5. Verify AJAX requests work properly
6. Test with different WordPress versions
7. Check plugin compatibility with other plugins

## Common Patterns to Follow

### Database Query Pattern
```php
global $wpdb;
$results = $wpdb->get_results(
    $wpdb->prepare("SELECT * FROM {$table} WHERE id = %d", $id),
    ARRAY_A
);
```

### AJAX Handler Pattern
```php
public function ajax_handler() {
    if (!wp_verify_nonce($_POST['nonce'], 'action_nonce')) {
        wp_die('Security check failed');
    }
    
    if (!current_user_can('manage_woocommerce')) {
        wp_die('Insufficient permissions');
    }
    
    // Process request
    wp_send_json_success($data);
}
```

### HPOS Compatibility Pattern
```php
$hpos_enabled = class_exists('\Automattic\WooCommerce\Utilities\OrderUtil') && 
               \Automattic\WooCommerce\Utilities\OrderUtil::custom_orders_table_usage_is_enabled();

if ($hpos_enabled) {
    // HPOS query
} else {
    // Legacy query
}
```

## Plugin-Specific Guidelines
- Always check if Advanced Coupons plugin is active
- Use the virtual coupons table structure from Advanced Coupons
- Implement proper reasons for missing order IDs
- Show statistics cards for quick overview
- Use modal dialogs for detailed information
- Implement proper filtering and search functionality 